33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#if defined(BUILDING_V8_SHARED) && defined(USING_V8_SHARED)
39#error both BUILDING_V8_SHARED and USING_V8_SHARED are set - please check the\
40 build configuration to ensure that at most one of these is set
41#endif
42
43#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
44# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
45#elif USING_V8_SHARED
46# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
47#else
48# define V8_EXPORT
49#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
50
51#else // V8_OS_WIN
52
53// Setup for Linux shared library export.
54#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY && defined(V8_SHARED)
55# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
56# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
57# else
58# define V8_EXPORT
59# endif
60#else
61# define V8_EXPORT
62#endif
63
64#endif // V8_OS_WIN

164class UniqueId {
165 public:
166 explicit UniqueId(intptr_t data)
167 : data_(data) {}
168
169 bool operator==(const UniqueId& other) const {
170 return data_ == other.data_;
171 }
172
173 bool operator!=(const UniqueId& other) const {
174 return data_ != other.data_;
175 }
176
177 bool operator<(const UniqueId& other) const {
178 return data_ < other.data_;
179 }
180
181 private:
182 intptr_t data_;
183};

187#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
188 while (false) { \
189 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
190 }

218template <class T>
219class Local {
220 public:
221 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
222 template <class S>
223 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
224 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
230 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
231 }
232
236 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
237
241 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
242
243 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
244
245 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
246
253 template <class S>
254 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
255 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
256 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
257 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
258 if (b == 0) return false;
259 return *a == *b;
260 }
261
262 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
263 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
264 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
265 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
266 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
267 if (b == 0) return false;
268 return *a == *b;
269 }
270
277 template <class S>
278 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
279 return !operator==(that);
280 }
281
282 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
283 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
284 return !operator==(that);
285 }
286
287 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
288#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
289 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
290 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
291 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
292#endif
293 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
294 }
295
296 template <class S>
297 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
298 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
299 }
300
306 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
307 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
308 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
309
310 private:
311 friend class Utils;
312 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
313 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
314 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
315 template<class F> friend class Local;
316 template <class F>
317 friend class MaybeLocal;
318 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
319 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
320 friend class String;
321 friend class Object;
322 friend class Context;
323 friend class Private;
324 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
325 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
326 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
327 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
328 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
329 friend class HandleScope;
330 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
331 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
332 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
333 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
334 template <class F>
335 friend class ReturnValue;
336
337 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
338 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
339 T* val_;
340};

360template <class T>
361class MaybeLocal {
362 public:
363 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
364 template <class S>
365 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
366 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
367 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
368 }
369
370 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
371
372 template <class S>
373 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
374 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
375 return !IsEmpty();
376 }
377
378 // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
379 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
380
381 template <class S>
382 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
383 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
384 }
385
386 private:
387 T* val_;
388};

391// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.
392template <class T> class Eternal {
393 public:
394 V8_INLINE Eternal() : index_(kInitialValue) { }
395 template<class S>
396 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : index_(kInitialValue) {
397 Set(isolate, handle);
398 }
399 // Can only be safely called if already set.
400 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate);
401 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() { return index_ == kInitialValue; }
402 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
403
404 private:
405 static const int kInitialValue = -1;
406 int index_;
407};

410static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
411
412
413template <typename T>
414class WeakCallbackInfo {
415 public:
416 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
417
418 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
419 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
420 Callback* callback)
421 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
422 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
423 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
424 }
425 }
426
427 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
428 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
429 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
430
431 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
432 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
433 return internal_fields_[0];
434 }
435 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
436 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
437 return internal_fields_[1];
438 }
439
440 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
441 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
442 return callback_ != nullptr;
443 }
444
445 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
446 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
447 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
448 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
449 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
450 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
451 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
452
453 private:
454 Isolate* isolate_;
455 T* parameter_;
456 Callback* callback_;
457 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
458};
459
460
461// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
462// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
463// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
464// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
465// possible to request a second pass callback.
466enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

481template <class T> class PersistentBase {
482 public:
487 V8_INLINE void Reset();
492 template <class S>
493 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
494
499 template <class S>
500 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
501
502 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
503 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
504
505 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
506 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
507 }
508
509 template <class S>
510 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
511 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
512 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
513 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
514 if (b == NULL) return false;
515 return *a == *b;
516 }
517
518 template <class S>
519 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
520 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
521 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
522 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
523 if (b == NULL) return false;
524 return *a == *b;
525 }
526
527 template <class S>
528 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
529 return !operator==(that);
530 }
531
532 template <class S>
533 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
534 return !operator==(that);
535 }
536
544 template <typename P>
545 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
546 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
547 WeakCallbackType type);
548
556 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
557
558 template<typename P>
559 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
560
561 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
562 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
563
569 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate) const;
570
577 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
578
587 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED(
588 "deprecated optimization, do not use partially dependent groups",
589 void MarkPartiallyDependent());
590
596 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();
597
598 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
599
601 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
602
604 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
605
610 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
611
616 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
617
618 private:
619 friend class Isolate;
620 friend class Utils;
621 template<class F> friend class Local;
622 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
623 template <class F>
624 friend class Global;
625 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
626 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
627 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
628 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
629 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
630 friend class Object;
631
632 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
633 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
634 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
635 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
636
637 T* val_;
638};

688template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
689 public:
693 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
699 template <class S>
700 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
701 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
702 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
703 }
709 template <class S, class M2>
710 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
711 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
712 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
713 }
720 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
721 Copy(that);
722 }
723 template <class S, class M2>
724 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
725 Copy(that);
726 }
727 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
728 Copy(that);
729 return *this;
730 }
731 template <class S, class M2>
732 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
733 Copy(that);
734 return *this;
735 }
741 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
742 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
743 }
744
745 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
746 template <class S>
747 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
748#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
749 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
750 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
751 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
752#endif
753 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
754 }
755
756 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
757 template <class S>
758 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
759 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
760 }
761
762 private:
763 friend class Isolate;
764 friend class Utils;
765 template<class F> friend class Local;
766 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
767 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
768
769 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
770 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
771 template<class S, class M2>
772 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
773};

781template <class T>
782class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
783 public:
787 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
793 template <class S>
794 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
795 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
796 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
797 }
803 template <class S>
804 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
805 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
806 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
807 }
811 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
812 other.val_ = nullptr;
813 }
814 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
818 template <class S>
819 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
820 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
821 if (this != &rhs) {
822 this->Reset();
823 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
824 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
825 }
826 return *this;
827 }
831 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT

836 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;

982class ScriptOriginOptions {
983 public:
984 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_embedder_debug_script = false,
985 bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
986 bool is_opaque = false)
987 : flags_((is_embedder_debug_script ? kIsEmbedderDebugScript : 0) |
988 (is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
989 (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0)) {}
990 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
991 : flags_(flags &
992 (kIsEmbedderDebugScript | kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque)) {}
993 bool IsEmbedderDebugScript() const {
994 return (flags_ & kIsEmbedderDebugScript) != 0;
995 }
996 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
997 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
998 }
999 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1000 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1001
1002 private:
1003 enum {
1004 kIsEmbedderDebugScript = 1,
1005 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1 << 1,
1006 kIsOpaque = 1 << 2
1007 };
1008 const int flags_;
1009};

1014class ScriptOrigin {
1015 public:
1016 V8_INLINE ScriptOrigin(
1017 Local<Value> resource_name,
1018 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset = Local<Integer>(),

1116class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1117 public:
1125 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1126 enum BufferPolicy {
1127 BufferNotOwned,
1128 BufferOwned
1129 };
1130
1131 CachedData()
1132 : data(NULL),
1133 length(0),
1134 rejected(false),
1135 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1136
1137 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1138 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1139 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1140 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1141 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1142 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1143 ~CachedData();
1144 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1145 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1146 const uint8_t* data;
1147 int length;
1148 bool rejected;
1149 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1150
1151 private:
1152 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1153 CachedData(const CachedData&);
1154 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1155 };
1156
1160 class Source {
1161 public:
1162 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1163 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1164 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1165 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1166 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1167 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1168
1169 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1170 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1171 // alive.
1172 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1173
1174 private:
1175 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1176 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1177 Source(const Source&);
1178 Source& operator=(const Source&);
1179
1180 Local<String> source_string;
1181
1182 // Origin information
1183 Local<Value> resource_name;
1184 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1185 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1186 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1187 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1188
1189 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1190 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1191 // set when calling a compile method.
1192 CachedData* cached_data;
1193 };

1615// A StateTag represents a possible state of the VM.

1617
1618// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
1619// by the sampling profiler API.
1620struct RegisterState {
1621 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr) {}
1622 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
1623 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
1624 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
1625};

1632 // executing an external callback.

2460class V8_EXPORT Symbol : public Name {
2461 public:
2462 // Returns the print name string of the symbol, or undefined if none.
2463 Local<Value> Name() const;
2464
2465 // Create a symbol. If name is not empty, it will be used as the description.
2466 static Local<Symbol> New(Isolate* isolate,
2467 Local<String> name = Local<String>());
2468
2469 // Access global symbol registry.
2470 // Note that symbols created this way are never collected, so
2471 // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.
2472 // Also, there is only one global name space for the names used as keys.
2473 // To minimize the potential for clashes, use qualified names as keys.
2474 static Local<Symbol> For(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2475
2476 // Retrieve a global symbol. Similar to |For|, but using a separate
2477 // registry that is not accessible by (and cannot clash with) JavaScript code.
2478 static Local<Symbol> ForApi(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2479
2480 // Well-known symbols
2481 static Local<Symbol> GetIterator(Isolate* isolate);
2482 static Local<Symbol> GetUnscopables(Isolate* isolate);
2483 static Local<Symbol> GetToStringTag(Isolate* isolate);
2484 static Local<Symbol> GetIsConcatSpreadable(Isolate* isolate);
2485
2486 V8_INLINE static Symbol* Cast(v8::Value* obj);
2487
2488 private:
2489 Symbol();
2490 static void CheckCast(v8::Value* obj);
2491};

3140template<typename T>
3141class ReturnValue {
3142 public:
3143 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3144 : value_(that.value_) {
3145 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3146 }
3147 // Local setters
3148 template <typename S>
3149 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3150 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3151 template <typename S>
3152 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3153 template <typename S>
3154 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3155 // Fast primitive setters
3156 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3157 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3158 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3159 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3160 // Fast JS primitive setters
3161 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3162 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3163 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3164 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3165 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3166
3167 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3168 template <typename S>
3169 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3170
3171 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3172 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3173 // value.
3174 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3175
3176 private:
3177 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3178 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3179 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3180 template <class F, class G, class H>
3181 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3182 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3183 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3184 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3185 internal::Object** value_;
3186};

4621enum class PropertyHandlerFlags {
4622 kNone = 0,
4623 // See ALL_CAN_READ above.
4624 kAllCanRead = 1,
4625 // Will not call into interceptor for properties on the receiver or prototype
4626 // chain. Currently only valid for named interceptors.
4627 kNonMasking = 1 << 1,
4628 // Will not call into interceptor for symbol lookup. Only meaningful for
4629 // named interceptors.
4630 kOnlyInterceptStrings = 1 << 2,
4631};

4634struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
4635 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
4637 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = 0,
4638 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = 0,
4639 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = 0,
4640 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = 0,
4641 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = 0,
4642 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
4643 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
4644 : getter(getter),
4645 setter(setter),
4646 query(query),
4647 deleter(deleter),
4648 enumerator(enumerator),
4649 data(data),
4650 flags(flags) {}
4651
4652 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
4653 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
4654 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
4655 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
4656 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
4657 Local<Value> data;
4658 PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
4659};

4662struct IndexedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
4663 IndexedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
4665 IndexedPropertyGetterCallback getter = 0,
4666 IndexedPropertySetterCallback setter = 0,
4667 IndexedPropertyQueryCallback query = 0,
4668 IndexedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = 0,
4669 IndexedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = 0,

5384
5390struct JitCodeEvent {
5391 enum EventType {
5392 CODE_ADDED,
5393 CODE_MOVED,
5394 CODE_REMOVED,
5395 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
5396 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
5397 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
5398 };
5399 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
5400 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
5401 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
5402 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
5403 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
5404 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
5405
5406 // Type of event.
5407 EventType type;
5408 // Start of the instructions.
5409 void* code_start;
5410 // Size of the instructions.
5411 size_t code_len;
5412 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
5413 Local<UnboundScript> script;
5414 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
5415 // code line information which is returned from the
5416 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
5417 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
5418 void* user_data;
5419
5420 struct name_t {
5421 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
5422 // zero-terminated.
5423 const char* str;
5424 // Number of chars in str.
5425 size_t len;
5426 };
5427
5428 struct line_info_t {
5429 // PC offset
5430 size_t offset;
5431 // Code postion
5432 size_t pos;
5433 // The position type.
5434 PositionType position_type;
5435 };
5436
5437 union {
5438 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
5439 struct name_t name;
5440
5441 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
5442 struct line_info_t line_info;
5443
5444 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
5445 void* new_code_start;
5446 };
5447};
5448
5454enum RAILMode {
5455 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
5456 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
5457 // Throughput may be throttled.
5458 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
5459 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
5460 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
5461 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
5462 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
5463 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
5464 // in this mode.
5465 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
5466 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
5467 // turn off latency optimizations.
5468 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
5469};
5470

6946template <class T>
6947class Maybe {
6948 public:
6949 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
6950 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
6951
6952 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6953 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
6954
6955 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
6956 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
6957 return IsJust();
6958 }
6959
6960 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6961 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6962 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6963 return value_;
6964 }
6965
6966 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6967 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
6968 }
6969
6970 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6971 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6972 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6973 }
6974
6975 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6976 return !operator==(other);
6977 }
6978
6979 private:
6980 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
6981 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
6982
6983 bool has_value_;
6984 T value_;
6985
6986 template <class U>
6987 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6988 template <class U>
6989 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6990};
6991
6992
6993template <class T>
6994inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6995 return Maybe<T>();
6996}
6997
6998
6999template <class T>
7000inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
7001 return Maybe<T>(t);
7002}

7514// --- Implementation ---
7515
7516
7517namespace internal {
7518
7519const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
7520const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
7521const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
7522
7523// Tag information for HeapObject.
7524const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
7525const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
7526const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
7527
7528// Tag information for Smi.
7529const int kSmiTag = 0;
7530const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
7531const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
7532
7533template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
7534
7535template<int kSmiShiftSize>
7536V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7537 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7538 uintptr_t tagged_value =
7539 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
7540 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
7541}
7542
7543// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
7544template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7545 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7546 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7547 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7548 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7549 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7550 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7551 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7552 }
7553 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7554 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7555 }
7556 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7557 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7558 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7559 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7560 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7561 //
7562 // CAUTION: The original code below:
7563 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7564 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7565 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7566 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7567 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7568 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7569 }
7570};
7571
7572// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7573template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7574 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7575 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7576 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7577 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7578 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7579 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7580 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7581 }
7582 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7583 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7584 }
7585 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7586 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7587 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7588 }
7589};
7590
7591typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
7592const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
7593const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
7594V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7595V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }
7596
7602class Internals {
7603 public:
7604 // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
7605 // the implementation of v8.
7606 static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
7607 static const int kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset =
7608 1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
7609 static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
7610
7611 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + sizeof(double);
7612 static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
7613 static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
7614 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
7615 static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
7616 static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 5;
7617 static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x07;
7618 static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x4;
7619 static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
7620 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x06;
7621
7622 static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
7623 static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
7624 static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
7625 kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
7626 static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
7627 kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
7628 kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;
7629 static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 4;
7630 static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
7631 static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;
7632 static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 7;
7633 static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;
7634 static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 9;
7635
7636 static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
7637 static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
7638 static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
7639 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
7640 static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
7641 static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
7642 static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
7643 static const int kNodeIsPartiallyDependentShift = 4;
7644 static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;
7645
7646 static const int kJSObjectType = 0xb7;
7647 static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0xb6;
7648 static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
7649 static const int kOddballType = 0x83;
7650 static const int kForeignType = 0x87;
7651
7652 static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
7653 static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;
7654
7655 static const uint32_t kNumIsolateDataSlots = 4;
7656
7657 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
7658 V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
7659#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7660 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
7661#endif
7662 }
7663
7664 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
7665 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
7666 kHeapObjectTag);
7667 }
7668
7669 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
7670 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
7671 }
7672
7673 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7674 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
7675 }
7676
7677 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7678 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
7679 }
7680
7681 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
7682 typedef internal::Object O;
7683 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
7684 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
7685 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
7686 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
7687 }
7688
7689 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
7690 typedef internal::Object O;
7691 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
7692 }
7693
7694 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
7695 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
7696 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
7697 }
7698
7699 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
7700 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7701 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7702 }
7703
7704 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
7705 bool value, int shift) {
7706 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7707 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7708 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
7709 }
7710
7711 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
7712 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7713 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
7714 }
7715
7716 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
7717 uint8_t value) {
7718 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7719 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
7720 }
7721
7722 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7723 uint32_t slot,
7724 void* data) {
7725 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
7726 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7727 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
7728 }
7729
7730 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
7731 uint32_t slot) {
7732 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
7733 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7734 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
7735 }
7736
7737 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7738 int index) {
7739 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
7740 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
7741 }
7742
7743 template <typename T>
7744 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
7745 const uint8_t* addr =
7746 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
7747 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
7748 }
7749
7750 template <typename T>
7751 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
7752 typedef internal::Object O;
7753 typedef internal::Internals I;
7754 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
7755 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
7756 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
7757 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
7758 int value_offset =
7759 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7760 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
7761 }
7762};
7763
7764} // namespace internal

7833 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);

7835 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
7836 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
7837 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
7838 M::Copy(that, this);
7839}

7842template <class T>
7843bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
7844 typedef internal::Internals I;
7845 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7846 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
7847 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
7848}

7851template <class T>
7852bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
7853 typedef internal::Internals I;
7854 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7855 uint8_t node_state =
7856 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
7857 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
7858 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
7859}

7864 typedef internal::Internals I;
7865 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7866 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
7867 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
7868}

7875 val_ = 0;
7876}

8016void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
8017 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
8018 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
8019}
8020
8021template<typename T>
8022void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
8023 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
8024 typedef internal::Internals I;
8025 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
8026 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
8027 return;
8028 }
8029 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
8030}
8031
8032template<typename T>
8033void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
8034 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
8035 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
8036 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
8037 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
8038 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
8039 return;
8040 }
8041 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
8042}
8043
8044template<typename T>
8045void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
8046 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
8047 typedef internal::Internals I;
8048 int root_index;
8049 if (value) {
8050 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
8051 } else {
8052 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
8053 }
8054 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
8055}
8056
8057template<typename T>
8058void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
8059 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
8060 typedef internal::Internals I;
8061 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
8062}
8063
8064template<typename T>
8065void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
8066 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
8067 typedef internal::Internals I;
8068 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
8069}
8070
8071template<typename T>
8072void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
8073 TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
8074 typedef internal::Internals I;
8075 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
8076}

8078template <typename T>
8079Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
8080 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
8081 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
8082}
8083
8084template <typename T>
8085Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
8086 typedef internal::Internals I;
8087 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
8088 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
8089 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
8090}

8096 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
8097}

8102 return value_[-1];

8248
8249Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
8250#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8251 typedef internal::Object O;
8252 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8253 typedef internal::Internals I;
8254 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8255 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8256 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8257 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8258 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8259 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
8260 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8261 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8262 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8263 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8264 }
8265#endif
8266 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8267}
8268
8269
8270void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
8271#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8272 typedef internal::Object O;
8273 typedef internal::Internals I;
8274 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8275 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8276 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8277 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8278 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8279 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
8280 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8281 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8282 }
8283#endif
8284 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8285}

8303
8304String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
8305 typedef internal::Object O;
8306 typedef internal::Internals I;
8307 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8308 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
8309 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
8310 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8311 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
8312 } else {
8313 result = NULL;
8314 }
8315#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8316 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
8317#endif
8318 return result;
8319}
8320
8321
8322String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
8323 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
8324 typedef internal::Object O;
8325 typedef internal::Internals I;
8326 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8327 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
8328 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
8329 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
8330 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
8331 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
8332 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8333 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
8334 }
8335#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8336 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
8337#endif
8338 return resource;
8339}

8831
8832int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8833 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8834 typedef internal::Internals I;
8835 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8836 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
8837 const int64_t external_memory_limit = *reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8838 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
8839 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
8840 *external_memory = amount;
8841 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > external_memory_limit) {
8842 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8843 }
8844 return *external_memory;
8845}
